Petrol Holding Stake May Be Sold By NLB, Istrabenz, Finance Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-02-17T08:42:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/petrol-holding-stake-may-be-sold-by-nlb-istrabenz-finance-says.html
Nova Ljubljanska Banka d.d. and  Istrabenz  Group d.d. may put a combined 10 percent stake in  Slovenia ’s Petrol Group d.d. up for sale, Finance newspaper
 reported , without saying where it got the information.  Istrabenz, which is in receivership, and NLB, as Slovenia’s
biggest bank is known, may as much as a combined 25 percent if
other Petrol investors join, the Ljubljana-based newspaper said.  An adviser in the sale will be picked up next month,
according to Finance.  NLB yesterday sold a 4 percent stake in Slovenia’s biggest
energy company and owns a 6 percent holding after the
transaction.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana, Slovenia, at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  